Ninety percent of the world&rsquo;s data was created in the last two years. That&rsquo;s 2.5 quadrillion bytes of data. For reference, the whole of Wikipedia takes up approximately 45GB of storage - less storage than the cheapest iPhone 8 ships with. As time goes on the amount of data and the rate of generation is only going to increase as more &lsquo;things&rsquo; connect to the internet.
